data.title: Monsieur Vincent (1947)
data.meta_description: An Academy Award winner for best Foreign Lanaguage Film, Monsieur Vincent chronicles the remarkable journey of St. Vincent de Paul who rose from slavery to become a trusted advisor to queens and princes. Director Maurice Cloche's powerful and dramatic biopic reveals how St. Vincent de Paul's unwavering commitment to the poor made him one of the greatest humanitarians in history.
data.text:
Read more

An Academy Award winner for best Foreign Lanaguage Film, Monsieur Vincent chronicles the remarkable journey of St. Vincent de Paul who rose from slavery to become a trusted advisor to queens and princes. Director Maurice Cloche's powerful and dramatic biopic reveals how St. Vincent de Paul's unwavering commitment to the poor made him one of the greatest humanitarians in history.
